        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Based on the `SKILL.md` files found in the `skills/` directory of your workspace, here are the skills defined in this project:\n\n### 1. **gcp-terraform-cicd** (Terraform GCP Skill)\n*   **Description:** Architect, provision, and troubleshoot production-grade Google Cloud infrastructure using Terraform and OpenTofu. Use this to design landing zones (Shared VPCs, Folders), deploy core services (GKE, Cloud Run, Cloud SQL), implement IAM least-privilege, and manage GCS-backed state. It enforces Google’s Cloud Foundation Fabric patterns and rigorous validation protocols to ensure secure, idempotent, and scalable deployments across environments.\n*   **Key Features:** GCS backend & state management, live provider documentation lookup, IAM management guidelines, Cloud Build triggers with Developer Connect, and Terraform directory structure standards.\n\n### 2. **gcp-cicd-design** (Google Cloud CI/CD Assistant)\n*   **Description:** Design and implement a Google Cloud-based CI/CD pipeline. Use this when you want to build a new pipeline or design an architecture on GCP.\n*   **Key Features:** Operates in a two-stage workflow:\n    1.  **Architectural Design:** Gathers context, proposes deployment patterns (like trunk-based deployment), and drafts a `YAML` action plan collaboratively.\n    2.  **Plan Implementation:** Translates the approved plan into Terraform HCL or directly implements it sequentially using `gcloud` and specialized tools.\n\n### 3. **deploy-cicd-gcp** (Google Cloud CI/CD Assistant - Deployment)\n*   **Description:** Deploy an application to Google Cloud. Use this when you want to deploy a new application on GCP.\n*   **Key Features:** Analyzes the application type (Static Site vs. Dynamic Service) and follows one of three deployment workflows:\n    *   **Workflow A:** Deploys static applications to Google Cloud Storage.\n    *   **Workflow B:** Deploys container-based applications to Google Cloud Run using Google Cloud Buildpacks.\n    *   **Workflow C:** Builds a Docker image locally, pushes it to Artifact Registry, and deploys it to Google Cloud Run.\n\n### 4. **cloud-deploy-pipelines** (Cloud Deploy Pipelines)\n*   **Description:** Design Cloud Deploy delivery pipelines and manage releases when deploying applications to Cloud Run and Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE). Use this when you want to deploy applications to multiple environments (e.g., dev and prod), leverage deployment strategies (e.g., canary), or roll back automatically/manually upon failure.\n*   **Key Features:** Steps through designing `clouddeploy.yaml` for targets, pipelines, and automations (including observability alert policies). Also includes release management (creating, promoting, monitoring, and troubleshooting releases/rollouts) and `skaffold.yaml` generation.\n\nThese skills act as specialized workflows that the Gemini CLI can activate to help you build, design, and deploy GCP CI/CD infrastructure more efficiently.",
